"debt_to_equity":33.312,"enterprise_value":3413512448.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":9.963,"enterprise_to_revenue":0.645,"earnings_growth":0.0,"shares_outstanding":45943000.0,"float_shares":8419747.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.78198,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-0.318,"fifty_two_week_high":129.0,"fifty_two_week_low":56.78,"fifty_day_average":67.7994,"two_hundred_day_avg":93.5964,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":129.0,"all_time_low":56.78,"long_business_summary":"Nikhil Adhesives Limited manufactures and sells polymer emulsions and adhesives in India. The company operates in two segments, Manufacturing of Adhesives & Emulsions and Trading in Chemicals & Others. It offers rubber, lamination, sticker grade, and wood adhesives, as well as adhesive for manufacturing tapes, and adhesives for special applications and packaging industries; construction chemicals; paint emulsions comprising pure acrylic, styrene acrylic and Vam acrylic co-polymer, Vam-Veova co-polymer, TER-polymer, and polymer additives and powder; and polyvinyl actetate emulsion for textile finishing, textile binders for printing and flocking, and emulsion for carpet industries. The company also provides monomers, solvents, and chemicals, as well as opacifiers and opaque polymers. It offers its products under the Mahacol, Emdilith, Emditex, Emdicryl, and Emdibind brands. The company exports its products to Nepal, Taiwan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, the Philippines, and Kenya. Nikhil Adhesives Limited was incorporated in 1986 and is based in Mumbai, India."}}